\newlabel{fig:multiwavelength}{{3}{7}{Multi-wavelength data fusion in Chandra Deep Field South. Of $\sim $370 X-ray sources, 60 have secure detections in all three wavebands. These are classified as 41 AGN (68\%) and 19 stars (32\%). The lack of galaxies in this sample reflects the selection effect that extended galaxies are harder to match compactly across wavebands in deep fields}{figure.3}{}}
