\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {5}{\ignorespaces Causal inference analysis of 1,000 Gaia DR2 stars. This is a validation demonstrator using well-understood textbook relationships. ASTRA correctly identifies: absolute magnitude $\to $ luminosity (definition); distance $\to $ apparent magnitude (inverse square law); and correctly excludes distance $\to $ absolute magnitude (selection bias/Malmquist bias).}}{10}{figure.5}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:causal}{{5}{10}{Causal inference analysis of 1,000 Gaia DR2 stars. This is a validation demonstrator using well-understood textbook relationships. ASTRA correctly identifies: absolute magnitude $\to $ luminosity (definition); distance $\to $ apparent magnitude (inverse square law); and correctly excludes distance $\to $ absolute magnitude (selection bias/Malmquist bias)}{figure.5}{}}
